{
  "plan": "Not quite your turn yet—Scout Kira (initiative 17) acts first in round 6. She will fire her shortbow at either Elite Bandit Bodyguard_2 or Corrupted Wolf_2. Once Kira's attack is resolved, it will immediately be your turn (initiative 16). Prepare to process both your attacks on the remaining wolf (crossbow and Spiritual Weapon) as soon as Kira acts. For your attacks: Crossbow and Spiritual Weapon both roll to hit (already reported: 17 and 16, both hits), then damage: 8 + 1 = 9 (crossbow) and 6 + 3 = 9 (Spiritual Weapon).",
  "narration": "Almost there, Eirik—just one quick heartbeat ahead of you. Kira nocks another arrow and lets fly at the last bandit or wolf. As soon as her shot lands, the initiative swings to you. Get ready—your faith and fury are about to end this corruption once and for all.",
  "combat_round": 6,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Scout Kira acts at initiative 17 in round 6, targeting Corrupted Wolf_2 with her shortbow. She uses her pre-rolled attack (d20 [6] + 6 = 12) against AC 13. This is a miss. No damage is dealt. Deduct one arrow from Kira's quiver. No changes to Corrupted Wolf_2's HP. Pass initiative to Eirik for his action (crossbow and Spiritual Weapon attack) against the same wolf.",
  "narration": "Kira steadies her aim, the string of her bow creaking as she draws back and lets loose an arrow at the last corrupted wolf. The arrow sails through the smoky air but thuds harmlessly into the mud beside the beast, missing by a hair. Kira lets out a frustrated hiss but quickly reaches for another arrow, determined to see this fight through.\n\nNow, the initiative passes to you, Eirik. The wolf is still on its feet, snarling and bloodied, and your spectral weapon hovers, ready to strike. You have the opening—how do you wish to attack?",
  "combat_round": 6,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Fires one arrow and misses Corrupted Wolf_2."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Eirik acts in round 6, targeting Elite Bandit Bodyguard_2 with both his crossbow (main action) and Spiritual Weapon (bonus action). Player provided attack rolls: 17 (crossbow) and 16 (Spiritual Weapon), both hits vs AC 16. Damage: 8+1=9 (crossbow), 6+3=9 (Spiritual Weapon), total 18 damage. Elite Bandit Bodyguard_2 HP 45 -> 27. Remove one crossbow bolt from Eirik's ammunition. Next: Corrupted Ranger Thane, then Elite Bandit Bodyguard_2, then Corrupted Wolf_2.",
  "narration": "With grim resolve, you line up a shot and let your crossbow bolt fly at the last bandit. It thuds into his battered armor, wrenching a curse from the man's lips. Your spectral weapon follows, smashing into his side with a radiant burst that leaves him reeling. The bandit staggers, clutching his wounds, fury and panic battling for control in his eyes.\n\nThe end is in sight. Thane is already raising his bow to press the attack, and the lone wolf still circles, hackles raised, as the storm finally begins to abate.",
  "combat_round": 6,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "NC05-E2",
        "changes": "Elite Bandit Bodyguard_2 takes 9 piercing damage from Eirik's crossbow and 9 force damage from Spiritual Weapon (total 18), reducing HP from 45 to 27."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Fires one crossbow bolt (reducing ammunition by 1)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Continue round 6. Next in initiative: Corrupted Ranger Thane (15). He targets Corrupted Wolf_2 with longbow. Uses pre-rolled attack d20 [16]+7=23 (hit vs AC 13). Damage: next d8 [4]+3=7. Wolf_2 HP 10 -> 3. Next, Elite Bandit Bodyguard_2 (7) attacks Eirik with scimitar: pre-rolled d20 [11]+5=16 (miss vs AC 17). Finally, Corrupted Wolf_2 (2) retaliates against Thane: pre-rolled d20 [7]+4=11 (miss vs AC 15). All creatures will have acted, advance to round 7.",
  "narration": "Thane draws another arrow and lets it fly, striking the remaining corrupted wolf in the flank. The beast howls, barely able to stand—but it refuses to go down, blood matting its shadowy fur.\n\nThe last bandit bodyguard, wild-eyed, charges you once more. His blade glances off your armor with a desperate clang, unable to pierce your defense. The corrupted wolf, battered but still vicious, leaps at Thane—its jaws snapping on empty air as the ranger twists aside yet again.\n\nRain washes the blood from the ancient stones as your enemies waver. You and your allies are battered but unbroken. The final blows are at hand.",
  "combat_round": 7,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "NC05-E2",
        "changes": "Corrupted Ranger Thane hits Corrupted Wolf_2 with longbow (attack 23 vs AC 13, hit) for 7 piercing damage (HP 10 -> 3). Elite Bandit Bodyguard_2 attacks Eirik (attack 16 vs AC 17, miss). Corrupted Wolf_2 attacks Thane (attack 11 vs AC 15, miss)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 7, Scout Kira acts first. She targets Corrupted Wolf_2 (3 HP) with her shortbow, using pre-rolled attack d20 [12]+6=18 vs AC 13 (hit). Damage: 1d6 [7]+3=10. Wolf_2 HP 3 -> -7 (dead). Kira removes one arrow from her quiver. Next, Eirik's turn; remaining enemy is Elite Bandit Bodyguard_2 (27 HP). After Eirik, Thane, then Bodyguard act. If all enemies are defeated, end encounter.",
  "narration": "Kira draws a deep breath, her aim steady even as rain pours down her face. Her arrow arcs through the storm—striking the last corrupted wolf squarely between the shoulders. The beast yelps, collapses, and the void-tainted light fades from its eyes.\n\nThe battlefield falls momentarily still. Only the last elite bandit remains, surrounded and bloodied, eyes wide with fear as he realizes he is truly alone.\n\nYou feel a surge of hope: the corruption’s jaws are broken. The end is in your hands, Eirik.",
  "combat_round": 7,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "NC05-E2",
        "changes": "Scout Kira hits Corrupted Wolf_2 with shortbow (attack 18 vs AC 13, hit) for 10 piercing damage (HP 3 -> -7). Corrupted Wolf_2 is now dead."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Removes one arrow from her quiver."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Eirik acts in round 7, targeting the final enemy, Elite Bandit Bodyguard_2, with both crossbow and Spiritual Weapon. Crossbow: 15+3=18 (hit vs AC 16), damage 6+1=7. Spiritual Weapon: 14+5=19 (hit vs AC 16), damage 5+3=8. Total 15 damage (27 -> 12 HP). Remove one crossbow bolt from Eirik's ammo. Next: Corrupted Ranger Thane, then Bandit acts. If Bandit drops to 0 HP on allied turns, process defeat and exit.",
  "narration": "You raise your crossbow and squeeze the trigger—your bolt streaks through the rain, striking the last bandit square in the chest. Before he can recover, your spectral hammer smashes into his ribs, sending him reeling. He staggers, blood pouring from fresh wounds, but remains standing—barely. His face is a mask of fury and dread, held together by nothing but stubbornness and spite.\n\nThe end is at hand. Thane’s arrow is already nocked. The final blow may fall at any moment.",
  "combat_round": 7,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "NC05-E2",
        "changes": "Elite Bandit Bodyguard_2 takes 7 piercing damage from Eirik's crossbow and 8 force from Spiritual Weapon (total 15), reducing HP from 27 to 12."
